      <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
         <head>Biographical History</head>
         
      <p>Mildred Batchelder (1901-1988) was an American librarian and author, and an energetic advocate for children's literature and services.  The Mildred L. Batchelder Award, given each year to the publisher of the most outstanding children's book translated into English, is named for her.</p></bioghist>
      
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
         <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
         <p>The <emph render="bold">Mildred Batchelder Collection</emph> consists of two items relating to Batchelder's book <emph render="italic">The Children's World of Books</emph>.</p>
      </scopecontent>
      
